@startuml OmniEdgeAI_Architecture

title OmniEdge_AI v2.3 — System Architecture & Interaction Flow\n12 Independent C++ Processes · WSL2 · NVIDIA RTX PRO 3000 Blackwell (12 GB) · 4 GPU Tiers
autonumber

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam maxmessagesize 240
skinparam sequenceParticipant underline
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #616161
skinparam sequenceGroupHeaderFontSize 13

' ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
' Participants — each box is an independent OS process.
' IPC: ZeroMQ (control) + POSIX SHM (data). No shared libs.
' All modules use MessageRouter for consolidated ZMQ management.
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

box "Ingestion" #E8F5E9
    participant "Video Ingest\nGStreamer · Port 5555" as GSV
    participant "Audio Ingest\nGStreamer+VAD · Port 5556" as GSA
end box

box "ZMQ PUB/SUB Bus" #FFF3E0
    participant "ZeroMQ\nTCP localhost" as ZMQ
end box

box "Vision Nodes" #FCE4EC
    participant "Face Recog\nInspireFace FP16\n0.5 GB · Port 5566" as FR
    participant "Background Blur\nYOLOv8-seg FP16\n0.5 GB · Port 5567" as BB
    participant "VLM\nMoondream2 INT4\n2.45 GB · Port 5562" as VLM
end box

box "Audio / Language Nodes" #E3F2FD
    participant "STT\nWhisper V3 INT8\n1.5 GB · Port 5563" as STT
    participant "LLM\nQwen 2.5 7B INT4\n4.3 GB · Port 5561" as LLM
    participant "TTS\nKokoro v1.0 INT8\n0.1 GB · Port 5565" as TTS
end box

box "Enhancement Nodes (On-Demand)" #E8EAF6
    participant "Video Denoise\nBasicVSR++ FP16\n1.5 GB · Port 5568" as VDN
    participant "Audio Denoise\nDTLN FP32\n0.05 GB · Port 5569" as ADN
end box

box "Frontend" #F3E5F5
    participant "WS Bridge\nuWebSockets :9001\nPort 5570" as UWS
    participant "Browser\nCanvas + AudioCtx" as UI
end box

box "Daemon" #EFEBE9
    participant "OmniEdgeDaemon\nWatchdog · Port 5571" as DAEMON
end box


note over DAEMON, UWS
  All modules use **MessageRouter**
  (common/networking/message_router.hpp)
  for consolidated ZMQ PUB/SUB management.
  One MessageRouter per process replaces
  manual ZMQ context, sockets, and poll loop.
end note


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 1 — SYSTEM BOOT
' ==============================================================

== Phase 1: System Boot — Daemon Spawns All Processes ==

note over DAEMON
  **oe_daemon** is the only binary the user starts.
  Reads omniedge_config.yaml, probes GPU via NVML,
  selects tier (minimal/balanced/standard/ultra),
  then spawns each module via posix_spawn().
  Each child = independent ELF binary with own main().
  **Each process creates its own CUDA context
  via cudaSetDevice(0). No MPS, no CUDA IPC.
  WDDM time-slices contexts on the GPU.**
end note

DAEMON -> UWS : posix_spawn("oe_ws_bridge")
note right: Launched FIRST — relays module_ready events

DAEMON -> GSV : posix_spawn("oe_video_ingest")
DAEMON -> GSA : posix_spawn("oe_audio_ingest")
DAEMON -> BB  : posix_spawn("oe_bg_blur")
DAEMON -> FR  : posix_spawn("oe_face_recog")
DAEMON -> STT : posix_spawn("oe_stt")
DAEMON -> TTS : posix_spawn("oe_tts")
DAEMON -> LLM : posix_spawn("oe_llm")

note over DAEMON
  Each module initializes → loads TRT/ONNX engine
  → MessageRouter binds PUB → publishes module_ready.
  Daemon waits 30 s per module, proceeds without
  stragglers. Then enters watchdog + state machine loop.
  **7-state FSM:** IDLE · LISTENING · PROCESSING ·
  PROCESSING_VISION · SPEAKING · INTERRUPTED · ERROR_RECOVERY
end note


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 2 — BROWSER CONNECTS
' ==============================================================

== Phase 2: Browser Connects — 5 WebSocket Channels ==

UI -> UWS : new WebSocket("/video")   [binary JPEG]
UI -> UWS : new WebSocket("/audio")   [binary PCM]
UI -> UWS : new WebSocket("/chat")    [bidirectional JSON]
UI -> UWS : new WebSocket("/denoise_video")   [binary JPEG, denoised]
UI -> UWS : new WebSocket("/denoise_audio")   [binary PCM, denoised]

note over UWS
  **C++ bridge threading:**
  Thread 1: uWS event loop (WebSocket I/O)
  Thread 2: MessageRouter::run() polls all SUB sockets
  Data bridged via queue + uWS::Loop::defer()

  **/denoise_video** and **/denoise_audio** are idle
  until the user toggles enhancement from the UI.
  The daemon spawns BasicVSR++ / DTLN on demand.
end note


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 3 — VIDEO PIPELINE
' ==============================================================

== Phase 3: Video — Webcam → GPU → JPEG → Canvas ==

group Video Ingest [oe_video_ingest]
    GSV -> GSV : GStreamer:\nv4l2src → jpegdec → videoconvert → BGR appsink
    GSV -> GSV : Write 6.2 MB BGR to /oe.vid.ingest\n(double-buffer, atomic writeIndex flip)
    GSV -> ZMQ : PUB "video_frame"\n{shm:"/oe.vid.ingest", seq:N}
end

note over ZMQ
  **ZMQ_CONFLATE=1** on data topics:
  video_frame, audio_chunk, blurred_frame, identity.
  **ZMQ_CONFLATE=0** on control topics:
  llm_prompt, transcription, ui_command, llm_response.
end note

group Face Recognition [oe_face_recog]
    ZMQ -> FR : SUB "video_frame" (5555)\n(every 3rd frame ~10 fps)
    FR -> FR : readLatestBgrFrame(shmIn_)\n→ BgrFrameView{data, w, h, slot}
    FR -> FR : backend_->detect(frame)\n→ bbox + 512-dim embedding
    FR -> FR : cosine sim vs SQLite gallery\n→ {name, confidence}
    FR -> ZMQ : PUB "identity"\n{name:"Admin", conf:0.98}
end

group Background Blur [oe_bg_blur — 5-step GPU pipeline]
    ZMQ -> BB : SUB "video_frame" (5555)
    ZMQ -> BB : SUB "ui_command" (5570)\n(set_image_adjust, update_shapes)
    BB -> BB : 1. Read BGR from SHM
    BB -> BB : 2. ISP: BCS + sharpen (GPU)
    BB -> BB : 3. YOLOv8-seg → person mask
    BB -> BB : 4. Gaussian blur compositing
    BB -> BB : 5. nvJPEG encode → /oe.cv.blur.jpeg
    BB -> ZMQ : PUB "blurred_frame"\n{shm:"/oe.cv.blur.jpeg", size:N}
end

group VLM [oe_vlm — on-demand or periodic]
    ZMQ -> VLM : SUB "video_frame" (5555)
    VLM -> VLM : SigLIP encode (378×378)\n→ [1, 729, 2048] features
    VLM -> VLM : Text decoder loop → description
    VLM -> ZMQ : PUB "vlm_description"\n{text:"Person at desk..."}
end

ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "blurred_frame" (5567)\nSUB "video_frame" (5555) [raw fallback]
UWS -> UI : /video: binary JPEG @ 30 fps\n→ Blob → canvas.drawImage()


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 4 — AUDIO PIPELINE
' ==============================================================

== Phase 4: Audio — Mic → VAD → STT → Daemon ==

group Audio Ingest + VAD [oe_audio_ingest]
    GSA -> GSA : GStreamer:\ntcpclientsrc :5001 → F32LE 16kHz mono
    GSA -> GSA : Silero VAD (CPU, <1 ms):\nspeech_prob > 0.5 → pass\nsilence → discard
    GSA -> GSA : Write PCM to /oe.aud.ingest
    GSA -> ZMQ : PUB "audio_chunk"\n{shm:"/oe.aud.ingest", vad:"speech"}
    GSA -> ZMQ : (on 800 ms silence)\nPUB "vad_status" {speaking:false}
end

group STT [oe_stt — Whisper V3 Turbo]
    ZMQ -> STT : SUB "audio_chunk" (5556)
    STT -> STT : Read PCM from SHM\n→ 128-bin Log-Mel spectrogram (CPU)
    STT -> STT : cudaMemcpyAsync → encoder → decoder
    STT -> STT : Hallucination filter:\nno_speech_prob > 0.6 → discard\nrepeat ≥ 3× → suppress
    STT -> ZMQ : PUB "transcription"\n{text:"Hello OmniEdge", lang:"en"}
end


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 5 — DAEMON ORCHESTRATION → LLM
' ==============================================================

== Phase 5: Daemon Orchestration — Prompt Assembly → LLM ==

note over DAEMON
  Daemon subscribes to ALL sensor outputs.
  Caches: latest identity, scene description.
  On new transcription → assembles full prompt
  → publishes "llm_prompt" to LLM.
  **LLM subscribes ONLY to daemon (port 5571).**
end note

group Prompt Assembly [oe_daemon — FSM]
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "transcription" (5563)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "identity" (5566)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "vlm_description" (5562)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "vad_status" (5556)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SUB "ui_command" (5570)

    DAEMON -> DAEMON : LISTENING → PROCESSING\nAssemble prompt: system (200 tok)\n+ identity (20) + scene (80)\n+ history (2796) + utterance (500)\n= 4096 token budget
    DAEMON -> ZMQ : PUB "llm_prompt" (5571)\n{system:..., user:..., identity:...,\nscene:..., history:[...]}
end

group LLM [oe_llm — Qwen 2.5 7B INT4-AWQ]
    ZMQ -> LLM : SUB "llm_prompt" (5571)
    LLM -> LLM : Tokenize → TRT-LLM GptSession\npaged KV cache (1.15 GB budget)\ntop-p=0.9, temp=0.7
    LLM -> ZMQ : PUB "llm_response" (streamed)\n{token:"Hello", finished:false}
    LLM -> ZMQ : {token:"", finished:true}
end


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 6 — TTS
' ==============================================================

== Phase 6: TTS — Sentence Streaming → Browser Audio ==

group TTS [oe_tts — Kokoro v1.0 INT8]
    ZMQ -> TTS : SUB "llm_response" (5561)
    TTS -> TTS : Accumulate tokens → sentence\n(split on . ? ! or finished)
    TTS -> TTS : espeak-ng G2P → phoneme IDs\nONNX Runtime → PCM F32 @ 24 kHz
    TTS -> TTS : Write PCM to /oe.aud.tts
    TTS -> ZMQ : PUB "tts_audio"\n{shm:"/oe.aud.tts", rate:24000}
end

ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "tts_audio" (5565)
UWS -> UI : /audio: binary PCM\n→ AudioContext @ 24 kHz


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 7 — CHAT STREAMING
' ==============================================================

== Phase 7: Chat — Streamed Tokens → Browser ==

ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "llm_response" (5561)
UWS -> UI : /chat: JSON {token, finished}\n→ append to chat bubble


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 8 — USER ACTIONS
' ==============================================================

== Phase 8: User Actions — Browser → Backend ==

note over UI
  All UI interactions follow one pattern:
  JS event → WebSocket JSON → uWS parse
  → ZMQ PUB "ui_command" → target module
end note

' ── Push-to-Talk ──
group Push-to-Talk #FFEBEE
    UI -> UWS : {action:"push_to_talk", state:true}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : FSM: IDLE → LISTENING
    note over DAEMON: Audio capture begins
    UI -> UWS : {action:"push_to_talk", state:false}
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : FSM: LISTENING → PROCESSING\n→ prompt assembly → LLM
end

' ── Text Input ──
group Text Input #E8F5E9
    UI -> UWS : {action:"text_input", text:"..."}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : Bypass STT: IDLE → PROCESSING\nassemblePrompt(text) → LLM
end

' ── Describe Scene ──
group Describe Scene #FFF3E0
    UI -> UWS : {action:"describe_scene"}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (5570)
    ZMQ -> VLM : force immediate inference
    VLM -> ZMQ : PUB "vlm_description"
    ZMQ -> UWS : relay to browser
    UWS -> UI : {type:"vlm", text:"..."}
end

' ── Register Face ──
group Register Face #F3E5F5
    UI -> UWS : {action:"register_face",\nname:"Admin", image:<JPEG>}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (5570)
    ZMQ -> FR : detect → align → embed\n→ INSERT INTO known_faces
    FR -> ZMQ : PUB "face_registered"\n{name:"Admin", success:true}
    ZMQ -> UWS : relay confirmation
    UWS -> UI : showToast("Face registered")
end

' ── Image Adjustments ──
group Image Adjustments #E0F7FA
    UI -> UWS : {action:"set_image_adjust",\nadjust:{brightness, contrast,\nsaturation, sharpness}}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (5570)
    ZMQ -> BB : Update ISP params atomically\n(skipped if all defaults)
end

' ── Barge-In ──
group Barge-In Interruption #FFCDD2
    note over DAEMON: PTT during SPEAKING state
    UI -> UWS : {action:"push_to_talk", state:true}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : SPEAKING → INTERRUPTED
    DAEMON -> ZMQ : cancel_generation → LLM\nflush_tts → TTS\nstop_playback → Browser
    ZMQ -> LLM : stop token loop
    ZMQ -> TTS : clear sentence queue
    ZMQ -> UWS : stop_playback
    UWS -> UI : audioQueue=[]; reset AudioCtx
    DAEMON -> DAEMON : INTERRUPTED → LISTENING
end


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 8b — VIDEO/AUDIO DENOISING (ON-DEMAND)
' ==============================================================

== Phase 8b: Video/Audio Denoising (On-Demand) ==

note over VDN, ADN
  Enhancement modules are **not loaded at boot**.
  Daemon spawns them on-demand when the user
  toggles denoising from the web UI.
  Eviction priority 0 (evicted first).
end note

' ── Toggle Video Denoise ──
group Video Denoise Toggle #E8EAF6
    UI -> UWS : {action:"toggle_video_denoise", enabled:true}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : handleOnDemandRequest("video_denoise")
    DAEMON -> DAEMON : probeGpu(0).freeMb ≥ 1500?\nYES → spawn | NO → evict lowest priority
    DAEMON -> VDN : posix_spawn("oe_video_denoise")
    VDN -> ZMQ : PUB "module_ready"
end

group Video Denoise Pipeline [oe_video_denoise]
    ZMQ -> VDN : SUB "video_frame" (5555)
    VDN -> VDN : Read BGR from /oe.vid.ingest SHM\n→ 5-frame temporal ring buffer
    VDN -> VDN : BasicVSR++ ONNX inference\n(bidirectional propagation,\nflow-guided deformable alignment)
    VDN -> VDN : nvJPEG encode → /oe.vid.denoise SHM
    VDN -> ZMQ : PUB "denoised_frame"\n{shm:"/oe.vid.denoise", size:N}
end

ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "denoised_frame" (5568)
UWS -> UI : /denoise_video: binary JPEG\n→ Blob → second canvas (split-screen)

' ── Toggle Audio Denoise ──
group Audio Denoise Toggle #E8EAF6
    UI -> UWS : {action:"toggle_audio_denoise", enabled:true}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : handleOnDemandRequest("audio_denoise")
    DAEMON -> ADN : posix_spawn("oe_audio_denoise")
    ADN -> ZMQ : PUB "module_ready"
end

group Audio Denoise Pipeline [oe_audio_denoise]
    ZMQ -> ADN : SUB "audio_chunk" (5556)
    ADN -> ADN : Read PCM from /oe.aud.ingest SHM
    ADN -> ADN : DTLN Stage 1: separation network\n(STFT magnitude domain, LSTM)
    ADN -> ADN : DTLN Stage 2: signal reconstruction\n(complex spectrum domain, LSTM)
    ADN -> ADN : Write PCM to /oe.aud.denoise SHM
    ADN -> ZMQ : PUB "denoised_audio"\n{shm:"/oe.aud.denoise", samples:N}
end

ZMQ -> UWS : SUB "denoised_audio" (5569)
UWS -> UI : /denoise_audio: binary PCM\n→ AudioContext A/B comparison


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 9 — WATCHDOG & FAULT TOLERANCE
' ==============================================================

== Phase 9: Watchdog — Heartbeat & Auto-Recovery ==

note over DAEMON
  **ZMTP PING/PONG** (runs in ZMQ I/O thread —
  works even during CUDA kernel execution):
  ZMQ_HEARTBEAT_IVL      = 1000 ms
  ZMQ_HEARTBEAT_TIMEOUT  = 5000 ms
  ZMQ_HEARTBEAT_TTL      = 10000 ms
end note

loop Every 1000 ms (ZMTP automatic)
    DAEMON --> FR  : PING
    FR     --> DAEMON : PONG
    DAEMON --> LLM : PING
    LLM    --> DAEMON : PONG
    note over DAEMON: Same for all active modules
end

== Failure Recovery Example ==

FR ->x FR : SIGSEGV (crash)
DAEMON --> FR : PING — no PONG within 5000 ms
DAEMON -> DAEMON : kill(pid, SIGTERM)\n→ waitpid (2 s) → SIGKILL if needed\nrestartCount++ (max 3)\nSIGKILL handles stuck CUDA kernels:\ndriver reclaims context + VRAM
DAEMON -> FR : posix_spawn("oe_face_recog")\nFresh CUDA context → clean VRAM
DAEMON -> UWS : PUB "module_status"\n{module:"face_recognition", status:"down"}
UWS -> UI : Graceful degradation:\nLLM prompt: "identity: unknown"

note over UI
  **Degradation matrix:**
  FR down → identity unknown
  Blur down → raw video passthrough
  STT down → text input fallback
  TTS down → text-only responses
  LLM down → "Restarting…" banner
  VLM down → Describe Scene disabled
  Video Denoise down → toggle disabled
  Audio Denoise down → toggle disabled
end note


' ==============================================================
' PHASE 10 — DYNAMIC VRAM MANAGEMENT
' ==============================================================

== Phase 10: Dynamic VRAM — On-Demand Spawn & Eviction ==

note over DAEMON
  **Process-level VRAM isolation:**
  Process exit → CUDA context destroyed →
  ALL VRAM freed as contiguous blocks.
  Zero fragmentation guaranteed.
end note

group On-Demand VLM [balanced tier example]
    UI -> UWS : {action:"describe_scene"}
    UWS -> ZMQ : PUB "ui_command" (5570)
    ZMQ -> DAEMON : handleOnDemandRequest("vlm")
    DAEMON -> DAEMON : probeGpu(0).freeMb ≥ 2450?\nYES → spawn | NO → evict lowest priority
    DAEMON -> VLM : posix_spawn("oe_vlm")
    VLM -> ZMQ : PUB "module_ready"
    ZMQ -> VLM : describe_scene request
    VLM -> ZMQ : PUB "vlm_description"
    DAEMON -> VLM : SIGTERM after result\nVRAM freed — zero fragmentation
end


' ==============================================================
' VRAM BUDGET NOTE
' ==============================================================

note across
  **VRAM Budget — Standard Tier (12 GB)**
  Qwen 2.5 7B INT4-AWQ ... 4.30 GB  │  InspireFace FP16 ...... 0.50 GB
  Moondream2 INT4 ........ 2.45 GB  │  YOLOv8-seg FP16 ....... 0.50 GB
  Whisper V3 Turbo INT8 .. 1.50 GB  │  Kokoro v1.0 INT8 ...... 0.10 GB
  Paged KV Cache ......... 1.15 GB  │  WSL2 System Buffer .... 1.50 GB

  **On-Demand Enhancement (not in default budget):**
  BasicVSR++ FP16 ........ 1.50 GB  │  DTLN FP32 ............. 0.05 GB

  **4 Tiers:** minimal (4 GB) · balanced (8 GB) · standard (12 GB) · ultra (16+ GB)
  Auto-selected via probeGpu() at boot. Override: oe_daemon --profile <tier>

  **Key Architectural Properties:**
  • Process-per-model (12 binaries): crash isolation + zero VRAM fragmentation
  • No CUDA MPS: fault isolation requires separate CUDA contexts (MPS → one fault kills all)
  • No CUDA IPC: cudaIpcGetMemHandle unsupported under WDDM (WSL2)
  • cudaHostAlloc only: cudaHostRegister unsupported under WDDM
  • Dual IPC: POSIX SHM (data, zero-copy) + ZeroMQ (control, JSON)
  • Backend interfaces: swap models via YAML config, no code changes
  • No hardcoded numbers: omniedge_config.yaml → per-module *_constants.hpp → oe_defaults.hpp
  • CMAKE_CUDA_ARCHITECTURES=75;80;86;89;90;100;120 (Turing→Blackwell) — TRT engines not GPU-portable
end note

@enduml
